HIGH LEVEL DESCRIPTION:

 this program works like the ls function iin Unix and lists all the 
 files in a directory. There 4 flags available that may be used in 
 combination. These include:
 -a flag: lists all files
 -l flag: prints all files along with owners, groups, ACL codes and so on
          That is it gives further details
 -r flag: reverse the order to print it from oldest to newest/
          from the opposite ordering of alphabets
 -t flag: sort by time of edit


 HOW TO COMPILE IT :
  Type make to compile.  The makefile has been generated by me

 HOW TO RUN IT:
  After making, type ./myls followed by flags as desired
  including -a, -l, -r, -t or a combination of those
  or just myls tto list files.
 NORMAL OUTPUT:
  ./myls              
